[13:46:57] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nThe email input is inside `div.mx-auto.mt-10.bg-primary` - so the selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` should match. But the issue is that the element may not be visible when the test runs (intersection observer / lazy loading). \n\nThe parent div has class `mx-auto mt-10 bg-primary px-4 pb-5 pt-3 text-center leading-[1.1875rem] text-white lg:px-24`. \n\nThe selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` should work since the element IS visible after scroll. The issue in the test is timing - the test scrolls and then immediately waits with 30s timeout, but the element may not be mounted initially.\n\nWait - looking again at the error: `locator('div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]').first()` - timeout 30000ms exceeded. But the element IS present on the page after scroll. Maybe the issue is that the test scrolls but the newsletter section is lazy-loaded via Builder.io and doesn't render until it's in the viewport. \n\nThe test already has retry logic scrolling 15 times and checking isVisible(). After that it calls `waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 })`. But line 414 shows `timeout: 30_000` - this might be the first waitFor before the retry loop.\n\nLet me check the full TC-83232 test code around lines 409-415 to understand the flow better.\n\nActually the real issue is: `div.bg-primary` - this class might not match because the actual classes are `mx-auto mt-10 bg-primary px-4 pb-5 pt-3 text-center...`. The CSS selector `div.bg-primary` should still match since it only requires `bg-primary` to be one of the classes.\n\nThe real problem might be browser rendering: the input IS in the DOM but may not be `visible` in the Playwright sense. Let me check if it's actually detached or just needs to be scrolled into view.\n\nFor the test fix approach, the key changes needed:\n1. **Newsletter (TC-83232)**: The selector seems correct (`div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]`), but the wait strategy needs improvement. Should use `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` on the section itself, then wait. Need to verify if the element needs to be scrolled into viewport to render.\n\n2. **Login (TC-83240)**: Navigate to `/auth/login` directly instead of `/myaccount`. The current code may already do this (need to check).\n\n3. **Store selector (TC-83238)**: The `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary` selector for \"Set your store\" - need to discover what the actual selector is on the PDP.\n\nLet me look at the PDP page to find the real store link selector.\n"}}
