[13:47:26] {"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/tests/home-page.spec.ts", "content": "399: test(\n400:     'TC-83232 — Newsletter signup in footer accepts valid email and redirects to confirmation @newsletter @footer',\n401:     async ({ page }) => {\n402:         // Override the global 60 s timeout: Builder.io networkidle can take 30 s,\n403:         // plus the retry loop (~15 s) and the final waitFor (45 s). 180 s is safe.\n404:         test.setTimeout(180_000);\n405: \n406:         const homePage = new HomePage(page);\n407:         const { newsletter } = homePageData;\n408: \n409:         await test.step('Navigate to homepage', async () => {\n410:             await homePage.navigate(homePageData.urls.home);\n411:         });\n412: \n413:         await test.step('Scroll to footer newsletter form', async () => {\n414:             // The newsletter section is Builder.io-driven: it is rendered as a\n415:             // direct child of <body> and requires both the page to be fully hydrated\n416:             // and a scroll-to-bottom to trigger intersection observers that mount it.\n417:             // Strategy:\n418:             //   1. Scroll window to the very bottom to trigger the observer.\n419:             //   2. Wait for network to settle so Builder.io lazy content can load.\n420:             //      Use a 30 s timeout (UAT is slow; 10 s was too short on CI).\n421:             //   3. Attempt scrollIntoViewIfNeeded on the locator itself (Playwright\n422:             //      forces the browser to bring the element into the viewport, which\n423:             //      re-triggers any intersection observer if the element exists in DOM).\n424:             //   4. Poll isVisible() in a retry loop with repeated scroll triggers for\n425:             //      up to ~15 s before the final waitFor.\n426:             await page.evaluate(() => window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight));\n427:             // Allow additional time for Builder.io content to be fetched and rendered.\n428:             await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle', { timeout: 30_000 }).catch(() => {});\n429:             await page.waitForTimeout(1_000);\n430: \n431:             // Repeat scroll to bottom in case the page grew after Builder.io rendered.\n432:             await page.evaluate(() => window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight));\n433:             await page.waitForTimeout(500);\n434: \n435:             // scrollIntoViewIfNeeded triggers intersection observers on elements\n436:             // already in the DOM but outside the viewport.\n437:             await homePage.newsletterEmailInput\n438:                 .scrollIntoViewIfNeeded({ timeout: 5_000 })\n439:                 .catch(() => undefined);\n440: \n441:             // Poll for visibility in a retry loop as a belt-and-suspenders guard.\n442:             // Increased retries and interval to handle slow UAT / CI environments.\n443:             for (let scrollAttempt = 0; scrollAttempt < 15; scrollAttempt++) {\n444:                 const inputVisible = await homePage.newsletterEmailInput\n445:                     .isVisible()\n446:                     .catch(() => false);\n447:                 if (inputVisible) break;\n448:                 await page.evaluate(() => window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight));\n449:                 await page.waitForTimeout(1_000);\n450:             }\n451: \n452:             await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 });\n453:         });\n454: \n455:         await test.step('Fill valid email in newsletter input', async () => {\n456:             await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.fill(newsletter.testEmail);\n457:         });\n458: \n459:         await test.step('Click SIGN UP button', async () => {\n460:             await homePage.newsletterSubmitButton.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });\n461:             await homePage.newsletterSubmitButton.click();\n462:         });\n463: \n464:         await test.step('Verify page redirects to /enewsletter-settings', async () => {\n465:             // Submit triggers a client-side navigation to /enewsletter-settings?email=<email>.\n466:             // This confirms the form was accepted and the user is routed to the preferences page.\n467:             await page.waitForURL(newsletter.expectedRedirectUrlPattern, { timeout: 45_000 });\n468:             await expect(page).toHaveURL(newsletter.expectedRedirectUrlPattern);\n469:         });\n470:     }\n471: );"}}
[13:47:40] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nThe error says line 414 `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 })` - but looking at the actual code, line 414 is a comment. The actual `waitFor` is at line 452 with `timeout: 45_000`. \n\nBut the error stacktrace says: `414 |             await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });` - this must be a different version of the file (the test was updated since the last run).\n\nWait - looking at the error message again:\n```\n412 |             // element to mount before interacting.\n413 |             await page.evaluate(() => window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight));\n> 414 |             await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });\n```\n\nThis is an OLDER version of the file. The current file has a different implementation with the retry loop. But the AGENTS.md says the tests are currently modified (gitStatus shows `tests/home-page.spec.ts (M)`). \n\nSo either:\n1. The tests shown in gitStatus have uncommitted changes (the current file I see is the NEW version with retry loop), OR\n2. The error was from a previous test run on an older version\n\nSince `tests/home-page.spec.ts (M)` is in the git status as modified, and the current file content (line 452) shows `timeout: 45_000`, the current code already has the improved retry logic. The failures might be from a PREVIOUS run before the improvements were committed.\n\nLet me check git status to understand which version caused these errors.\n\nActually, the task says \"FIx this issues\" - so the user wants me to fix these failures. The errors listed are from a recent test run. I need to investigate if the current code has these selectors already fixed or if they're still using the old selectors.\n\nLooking at the current code:\n- `tests/home-page.spec.ts` is M (modified) - so the file has changes not committed\n- `pages/LoginPage.ts` is M\n- `pages/ProductDetailPage.ts` is M\n\nThe error at line 414 in home-page.spec.ts matches an OLDER version. The current file at line 414 has a comment. So the test run that generated these errors used an older codebase version.\n\nHOWEVER - the user says \"Fix this issues\" so they want me to fix the failing tests. Let me check the current state of things by running the specific failing tests to see if they still fail.\n\nActually, I shouldn't run full tests (they take too long). Let me instead:\n1. Explore the live site to find the correct selectors for all 3 failing areas\n2. Fix the page objects and test files\n\nLet me check the PDP to find the real store selector.\n"}}
