":\\\"hover:underline\\\"},{\\\"index\\\":23,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Prescription Delivery\\\",\\\"class\\\":\\\"hover:underline\\\"},{\\\"index\\\":24,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Apple Service\\\",\\\"class\\\":\\\"hover:underline\\\"}]\"", "server_name": "mcp-web-inspector", "tool_name": "evaluate"}}
[13:51:08] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nExcellent! Now I can see the actual classes on the \"Set your store\" paragraph:\n- `class: \"mr-1 cursor-pointer text-primary underline\"`\n\nBut the current selector is `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary` - this should match! The element has `cursor-pointer` and `text-primary` in its class. However it also has `mr-1` and `underline`.\n\nWait - BUT this PDP has a STORE ALREADY SET (it shows \"Ready for pickup in 3-5 business days at My Store\" and \"Check Availability at other stores\"). \n\nThe \"Set your store\" text is at index 5, visible! But the class is `mr-1 cursor-pointer text-primary underline` - the selector `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary` should match this.\n\nNow looking at the openStoreSelectorDialog logic:\n1. Select in-store pickup radio → scroll into view → wait 2.5s\n2. Look for \"Set your store\" (5s timeout), if not visible look for \"Check Availability at other stores\" (15s timeout)\n\nThe issue with firefox/webkit could be that:\n1. The in-store pickup radio scroll + 2.5s wait isn't enough\n2. OR the browser-specific rendering of the fulfillment section takes longer\n3. OR the selector itself doesn't match in some state\n\nLooking at the current `openStoreSelectorDialog` code more carefully, it seems like it:\n1. First clicks in-store pickup radio (which might not be defined in this function)\n2. Scrolls it into view\n3. Waits 2.5s for intersection-observer\n4. Tries `setYourStoreLink` (5s), falls back to \"Check Availability at other stores\" (15s)\n\nThe issue: the main `openStoreSelectorDialog` function at line 270 uses only `setYourStoreLink` with 15s timeout (the error is at line 262), NOT the updated version with the fallback. Let me re-read the function.\n\nFrom earlier output:\n```\n270:    async openStoreSelectorDialog(): Promise<void> {\n...\n262:        await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });\n263:        await this.setYourStoreLink.click();\n264:        await this.storeSelectorDialog.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 10_000 });\n```\n\nWait, the error stacktrace says:\n```\n260 |      */\n261 |     async openStoreSelectorDialog(): Promise<void> {\n> 262 |         await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });\n     |                                     ^\n263 |         await this.setYourStoreLink.click();\n264 |         await this.storeSelectorDialog.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 10_000 });\n265 |     }\n```\n\nBUT the current modified ProductDetailPage.ts has the more complex version with the retry logic (lines 270-305 based on my earlier reading). The error was at LINE 262 of an older version.\n\nSo there are TWO versions of `openStoreSelectorDialog`:\n1. **OLD (from error log)**: Simple - just calls `setYourStoreLink.waitFor(15s)` at line 262\n2. **CURRENT (modified)**: Complex - with in-store pickup scroll, 2.5s wait, try/catch for set vs check availability\n\nThe current MODIFIED version is what's in the working tree. The error was from a previous run. So my job is to ensure the CURRENT code is correct.\n\nLooking at the current code: It tries `setYourStoreLink` for 5s, then falls back to \"Check Availability\" for 15s. BUT these are only tried AFTER:\n1. Clicking in-store pickup radio\n2. Scrolling it into view\n3. Waiting 2.5s\n\nBut wait - the test `TC-83238` calls `openStoreSelectorDialog` at line 171. Let me see the full test flow to understand what the current `openStoreSelectorDialog` function does and what state it expects.\n\nActually, let me look at the full current openStoreSelectorDialog method in the modified ProductDetailPage.ts.\n"}}
