[13:52:05] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nThe in-store pickup radio IS there: `input[aria-label=\"Product Ship to Store Pickup Fulfillment Type\"]` - matches the current selector.\n\nNow let me check the \"Set your store\" element more carefully. The PDP I'm on has a store pre-set (shows \"Ready for pickup in 3-5 business days at My Store\" and \"Check Availability at other stores\"). But the class on \"Set your store\" is `mr-1 cursor-pointer text-primary underline` and it's visible (index 5).\n\nWait - actually the current page state might differ from what the tests see:\n- If no store is set: \"Set your store\" is shown\n- If a store is already set: \"Check Availability at other stores\" is shown\n\nThe current code handles both cases. The issue for firefox/webkit must be something else.\n\nLooking at the error again: `waiting for locator('p.cursor-pointer.text-primary').filter({ hasText: /set your store/i }).first() to be visible` - this is the OLD selector at line 262.\n\nThe CURRENT modified code already has the fallback. So the errors were from an OLD run. The current modified code should work.\n\n**Summary of what the current modified files should fix:**\n\n1. **TC-83232 Newsletter** (home-page.spec.ts): \n   - Error was at line 414 with 30s timeout (old code)\n   - Current code: Has retry loop + 45s final waitFor at line 452\n   - The selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` is confirmed correct\n\n2. **TC-83240 Login** (LoginPage.ts):\n   - Error was at LoginPage.ts:28 with 15s timeout (old code)\n   - Current code: navigates to `/auth/login` directly, 45s timeout at line 43\n   - Email input `input[name=\"email\"][type=\"email\"]` is confirmed correct\n\n3. **TC-83238 Store selector** (ProductDetailPage.ts):\n   - Error was at line 262 with old simple `openStoreSelectorDialog`\n   - Current code: has fallback to \"Check Availability at other stores\"\n   - But the `setYourStoreLink` selector itself may still be an issue for firefox/webkit\n\nWait - I need to look at why the openStoreSelectorDialog error was specifically on firefox and webkit but not chromium. The current page I'm on shows \"Set your store\" IS visible - but maybe in the test environment the in-store pickup radio isn't present for all products.\n\nActually, on the current PDP page (vitamin water), the in-store pickup radio IS present and \"Set your store\" or \"Check Availability\" IS present. The issue for firefox/webkit might be:\n1. The product selected in the test may be different (different product found via search on FF/WK)\n2. The inStorePickupRadio.scrollIntoViewIfNeeded might fail on FF/WK\n3. The 2.5s wait isn't enough on FF/WK\n\nThe key insight: The current code at line 272 does `inStorePickupRadio.scrollIntoViewIfNeeded()`. If the in-store pickup radio isn't found (eg product doesn't support it), this fails silently (.catch(() => undefined)). Then after 2.5s wait, it looks for the store link. But if the product found in the search doesn't have in-store pickup available, neither the \"Set your store\" nor \"Check Availability\" links may appear.\n\nHowever, the more likely issue is timing. For firefox/webkit, the page hydrates slower, and 2.5s isn't enough for the fulfillment section to mount.\n\n**My fix plan:**\n1. The newsletter selector/timing - verify the current code is sufficient\n2. Login - verify the current code is sufficient  \n3. Store selector - increase the timeout/retry logic for firefox/webkit\n\nBut actually, looking at the error trace for issue 3:\n```\n> 262 |         await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });\n```\nThis is the OLD code. The CURRENT modified code at line 292 only waits 5s (with try/catch fallback). \n\nThe real question: **Are the current modified files already sufficient, or do they still have bugs?**\n\nLet me check if there are any remaining issues with the current code that need fixing.\n\nFor the store selector in the current c