[14:03:17] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nThe page snapshot for TC-83240 on Edge shows only `- img \"Loading...\"` - which means the page is stuck on a loading screen. The email input never appears even after 45s. \n\nThis is a real browser/page issue on Edge. The page at `/auth/login` gets stuck in a loading state. This could be:\n1. Edge browser having a different behavior with the UAT site\n2. A CORS or CSP issue specific to Edge\n3. The `waitForLoadState('networkidle')` is blocking, but since it has `.catch(() => {})`, it shouldn't block\n\nThe current code in LoginPage:\n```\nawait this.page.goto('/auth/login');\nawait this.page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\nawait this.page.waitForLoadState('networkidle', { timeout: 20_000 }).catch(() => {});\nawait this.emailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 });\n```\n\nThe page shows only a \"Loading...\" image - the React app hasn't hydrated. This is an Edge-specific issue.\n\nThe BasePage.waitForAppShell() waits for a `header` element. If the header never shows (Edge is slow hydrating), the method falls back and clicks body. But then when the LoginPage does `await this.page.goto('/auth/login')`, it doesn't call `this.navigate()` (which calls waitForAppShell). Instead it does a raw `page.goto` then `waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')`.\n\nFix idea: After navigating to `/auth/login`, call `this.waitForAppShell()` to ensure hydration completes, OR increase the networkidle timeout for Edge.\n\nBut actually - we can't just increase the timeout because on Edge the page is getting STUCK (only \"Loading...\" shows). This might be a rendering issue specific to Edge browser.\n\nAlternative approach for the login:\n1. Try navigating to `/auth/login` \n2. Wait for the header (app shell)\n3. If still loading, try clicking the body to dismiss any blocking overlay\n4. Wait for email input\n\nThe BasePage already has `dismissLoadingIfStuck()`. Perhaps I should use `this.navigate('/auth/login')` instead of `this.page.goto('/auth/login')` to leverage the full navigation stack with app shell waiting.\n\nActually the reason NOT to use `this.navigate()` was to avoid the double redirect. But `this.navigate()` goes to `/auth/login` directly, so there's no redirect issue.\n\nLet me try: change `this.page.goto('/auth/login')` to `this.navigate('/auth/login')` which includes:\n1. page.goto()\n2. waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n3. dismissLoadingIfStuck() - tries to click body if stuck\n4. waitForAppShell() - waits for header\n\nThis might help with the Edge loading issue.\n\nBut wait - `waitForAppShell` silently continues if header doesn't appear. So it won't block indefinitely. And `dismissLoadingIfStuck` clicks the body which might help dismiss the loading overlay.\n\nLet me make this change.\n"}}
