[14:07:28] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nThe TC-83232 newsletter test on Edge is now failing at a DIFFERENT step: \"Verify page redirects to /enewsletter-settings\" - `page.waitForURL: Timeout 45000ms exceeded`.\n\nThis is progress from the original error (which was at \"Scroll to footer newsletter form\"). Now the form IS found and filled, but after clicking \"SIGN UP\", the page doesn't redirect to `/enewsletter-settings` within 45s on Edge.\n\nThis is an **application behavior issue on Edge**: the newsletter signup form doesn't redirect properly on Edge, OR Edge is slow processing the redirect.\n\nPossible causes:\n1. Edge might block the redirect due to CSP/privacy settings\n2. The form submission might work differently on Edge\n3. The button click might not register properly on Edge\n\nThis is harder to fix because it's an actual application behavior (the redirect after form submit). This might be a legitimate cross-browser limitation on the UAT site.\n\nHowever, since this is specifically happening on Edge (chromium passes), it might be a timing issue - maybe Edge just needs more time for the redirect.\n\nWait - looking at the page snapshot after submit, it shows the home page header elements. This suggests either:\n1. The form submission was processed but the redirect didn't happen within 45s\n2. OR the newsletter email was already used (test reuse issue) so the redirect went somewhere else\n\nLooking at the test data: `newsletter.testEmail` - let me check what email is used.\n\nAlso, checking the test flow: After the form fill + click SIGN UP, the test expects redirect to `/enewsletter-settings?email=...`. If Edge is slower at processing the redirect (maybe it goes back to home page instead), we'd see this failure.\n\nActually, looking at the page snapshot - the page shows the HOME PAGE (London Drugs header, Select Your Store, etc.), not the enewsletter-settings page. This means either:\n1. The redirect went to home page (wrong behavior)\n2. The form submitted but redirected to a different URL than expected\n\nThe test uses:\n- `await page.waitForURL(newsletter.expectedRedirectUrlPattern, { timeout: 45_000 })`\n\nIf the actual redirect URL doesn't match the pattern, we'd get a different error. The `waitForURL` waits for the URL to MATCH the pattern. If the page stays on the home page or goes to a different URL, the timeout fires.\n\nThis could be because on Edge, the newsletter form submission is being blocked by browser-level tracking protection or some Edge-specific CSP issue, preventing the redirect.\n\nOne approach: mark TC-83232 on Edge as a browser-specific exception, OR skip it on Edge.\n\nBut actually, the better approach: check if the redirect happened to the right URL - maybe the timeout is just too short for Edge. Let me increase to 60s.\n\nOR - looking at this more carefully: after clicking SIGN UP, maybe the page needs a brief wait for the form processing before the redirect. Let me look at the test code.\n\nFrom the test at line 459-468:\n```\nawait test.step('Click SIGN UP button', async () => {\n    await homePage.newsletterSubmitButton.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 });\n    await homePage.newsletterSubmitButton.click();\n});\n\nawait test.step('Verify page redirects to /enewsletter-settings', async () => {\n    await page.waitForURL(newsletter.expectedRedirectUrlPattern, { timeout: 45_000 });\n    await expect(page).toHaveURL(newsletter.expectedRedirectUrlPattern);\n});\n```\n\nThe issue might be that on Edge, the button click doesn't actually submit the form (due to the `<a>` tag covering it per our earlier check_visibility finding). On Edge, the covered button might not receive the click properly.\n\nActually recall from earlier: `check_visibility` showed the newsletter email input is visible but \"covered by another element (`<a>` z-index: auto)\". This means the input IS visible but might not be interactable on Edge.\n\nHmm, but the test now passes the scroll/fill step and fails at the redirect step, so the fill at least works. The button might be different.\n\nLet me check if the newsletter submit button has the same coverage issue.\n\nAnother possibility: On Edge, the UAT site blocks the form submission due to browser-specific privacy/security settings.\n\nFor now, the best fix is to:\n1. Increase the waitForURL timeout from 45s to 60s for more robustness\n2. Or add a check to handle the case where the redirect doesn't happen\n\nActually, since this is a network/application issue on Edge browser, increasing the timeout is the most pragmatic fix. Let me increase to 60s.\n\nWait - but what if this is a genuine application bug on Edge? In that case, we might want to skip this test on Edge or add a `test.skip` condition.\n\nLet me think about what the right fix is. The test is checking that the newsletter form works. If it doesn't work on Edge due to browser behavior, we have two options:\n1. Skip on Edge\n2. Increase timeout hoping it's just slow\n\nGiven that the test IS completing the scroll + fill + click steps (the error is now ONLY at the redirect wait), it seems like the form submission is happening but the redirect is just slow on Edge (or the redirect URL doesn't match).\n\nLet me check what URL the pattern matches and if maybe the redirect is going somewhere slightly different.\n"}}
